                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d172">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">810.20 Defense/2581: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Colombia</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lane</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-05-20T20:00:00-04:00"
                            >May 20, 1942—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>591. The War Department and this Department are satisfied with the procedure
                    suggested in your 666 of May 18, 5 p.m. When you have seen President Santos it
                    is suggested that you inform General Andrews as well as the Department of the
                    substance of the understanding you may reach.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
